               <birth when="0475" syriaca-computed-start="0475-01-01" source="#bibl52-1">0475</birth>
               <death when="0538" syriaca-computed-start="0538-01-01" source="#bibl52-1">0538</death>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl52-1">Nau, dans ROC 7 (1902), 97-135 ; BHO, 497. J .W. Watt, dans J.W. Drijvers et J.W. Watt, eds., Portraits of Spiritual Authority (Leiden, 1999), 155- 69. BSO, I, lll2 (J .M. Fiey) .</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">John of Aphthonia was named after his mother who consecrated him to God.  He joined the monastery of St. Thomas in Seleucia.  He was later chased out of the area by Chalcedonians, and he founded the monastery of Qenneshrin on the Euphrates, across from Europos.  He wrote the Life of Severus of Antioch.   </note>
